channel.title: Data Types :: Java Web Development
channel.description: Static vs. Dynamic Typing In a dynamically typed programming language (like JavaScript or Python), a variable or parameter can refer to a value of any data type (string, number, object, etc.) at any time. When the variable is used, the interpreter figures out what type it is and behaves accordingly. Java is a statically typed language. When a variable or parameter is declared in a statically typed language, the data type for the value must be specified.
